from sekell subject re necessity of fuel injector clean by dealership in article jwg jim grey write in article prm write in ymy experience how true be it that a fuel injector clean will do much more good than just use detergent ga while i a fuel injector clean at the dealer be probably little more than them open ymy ga tank dump in a bottle of fuel injector cleaner and send you on ymy merry way poorer go to kmart and buy the cleaner yourself for thi should not be the case if they be at all reputable fuel injector clean be do properly with a can of injector cleaner solvent which be hook up to the fuel system under high pressure the car be actually run on the solvent during the clean proces the equipment to properly do thi be pricey and generally not something the average home mechanic ha the solvent itself be not very expensive and you could probably make up a hose to fit ymy system and do it yourself but i do tell you that not many in-tank cleaner be worth waste ymy money on there ha be a discussion of these product on here from time to time and chevron techron not pro-gard with techron be generally regard a the best it be however a bite more than a bottle imho it will not substitute for proper injector clean if they be really crudded up you have to decide if the price be a better deal than spend ymy time buy equipment to do it scott keller the agricultural group of monsanto company sekell packet 